		},
		{
			"id": 1,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "Autologous peripheral blood stem cell transplantation ( PBSCT ) is replacing autologous bone marrow transplantation ( BMT ) in the treatment of leukemia . <S>",
			"relation": "BACKGROUND"
		},
		{
			"id": 2,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "One of the potential advantages of autologous PBSCT is the possibility",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		},
		{
			"id": 3,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "that peripheral blood stem cells ( PBSC ) are less likely to be contaminated by leukemic cells than bone marrow grafts . <S>",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		},
		{
			"id": 4,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "However , the major problem still remains the high incidence of leukemic relapse",
			"relation": "COMPARISON"
		},
		{
			"id": 5,
			"parent": 4,
			"text": "following autologous PBSCT ,",
			"relation": "TEMPORAL"
		},
		{
			"id": 6,
			"parent": 4,
			"text": "which may be caused by the reinfusion of PBSC",
			"relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
		},
		{
			"id": 7,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "contaminated by leukemic cells . <S>",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		},
		{
			"id": 8,
			"parent": 0,
			"text": "Recently , we have developed a quantitative assay",
			"relation": "ROOT"
		},
		{
			"id": 9,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "using competitive reverse transcriptase polymerase chain reaction",
			"relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
		},
		{
			"id": 10,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "that estimates the number of AML1/ETO transcripts in t(8;21) acute myelogenous leukemia ( AML ) ,",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		},
		{
			"id": 11,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "in order to determine the degree of leukemic cell contamination in PBSC harvests ,",
			"relation": "ENABLEMENT"
		},
		{
			"id": 12,
			"parent": 11,
			"text": "and to monitor minimal residual disease ( MRD ) quantitatively in patients with t(8;21) AML . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION"
		},
		{
			"id": 13,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "Our data indicate that",
			"relation": "FINDINGS"
		},
		{
			"id": 14,
			"parent": 13,
			"text": "although PBSC harvests",
			"relation": "COMPARISON"
		},
		{
			"id": 15,
			"parent": 14,
			"text": "collected after consolidation chemotherapy",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		},
		{
			"id": 16,
			"parent": 14,
			"text": "are contaminated by leukemic cells ,",
			"relation": "SAME-UNIT"
		},
		{
			"id": 17,
			"parent": 13,
			"text": "the degree of leukemic cell contamination decreases with repeated cycles of chemotherapy . <S>",
			"relation": "SAME-UNIT"
		},
		{
			"id": 18,
			"parent": 13,
			"text": "Furthermore , the MRD in PBSC harvests is less than in the corresponding bone marrow",
			"relation": "ADDITION"
		},
		{
			"id": 19,
			"parent": 18,
			"text": "obtained on the day of the PBSC collection . <S>",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		},
		{
			"id": 20,
			"parent": 18,
			"text": "There appears to be no relationship between the number of AML1/ETO transcripts",
			"relation": "ADDITION"
		},
		{
			"id": 21,
			"parent": 20,
			"text": "found in the infused PBSC harvests",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		},
		{
			"id": 22,
			"parent": 20,
			"text": "and the incidence of leukemic relapse",
			"relation": "SAME-UNIT"
		},
		{
			"id": 23,
			"parent": 20,
			"text": "following autologous PBSCT in our study . <S>",
			"relation": "TEMPORAL"
		},
		{
			"id": 24,
			"parent": 20,
			"text": "However , a substantial decrease of AML1/ETO transcripts was seen",
			"relation": "COMPARISON"
		},
		{
			"id": 25,
			"parent": 24,
			"text": "following autologous PBSCT . <S>",
			"relation": "TEMPORAL"
		},
		{
			"id": 26,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "Thus , the quantitative analysis of AML1/ETO transcripts may be clinically useful in patients with t(8;21) AML . <S>",
			"relation": "FINDINGS"
		}
	]
}